00:31:15.600 --> 00:31:17.960
and we had two
number one albums.

00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:22.340
And as you can see on the stage,
I don't really hold my tongue.

00:31:22.340 --> 00:31:29.672
And there were some other people
in her life that were kind of--

00:31:29.672 --> 00:31:32.480
as you become more and more
popular and famous and more

00:31:32.480 --> 00:31:34.664
success, people just
start showing up.

00:31:34.664 --> 00:31:36.080
And they want to
create dissension

00:31:36.080 --> 00:31:38.810
because they want to create
opportunities for themselves.

00:31:38.810 --> 00:31:41.393
And there were people who were
creating dissension between she

00:31:41.393 --> 00:31:45.110
and I. And instead of just
kind of succumbing to that,

00:31:45.110 --> 00:31:49.210
I said what I felt.

00:31:49.210 --> 00:31:53.830
And in that confusion,
we went separate ways.

00:31:53.830 --> 00:31:57.670
And six months later
when those people

00:31:57.670 --> 00:32:01.000
showed their true colors, she
called me up and she said,

00:32:01.000 --> 00:32:02.340
can we meet?

00:32:02.340 --> 00:32:03.070
And we met up.

00:32:03.070 --> 00:32:06.610
And we had stayed cordial.

00:32:06.610 --> 00:32:07.750
And it was nothing.

00:32:07.750 --> 00:32:11.800
It was a hug, forgiven,
forgave each other for anything

00:32:11.800 --> 00:32:14.260
that was said, and back to it.

00:32:14.260 --> 00:32:16.000
And then we had
incredible success.

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:21.790
And then I'm sure
your next question

00:32:21.790 --> 00:32:26.497
is we went through some
really trying times together.

00:32:26.497 --> 00:32:27.330
JESSE MICHELS: Yeah.

00:32:27.330 --> 00:32:31.372
And talk about-- switching,
actually, to Kanye--

00:32:31.372 --> 00:32:33.205
SCOOTER BRAUN: Oh, I
thought you'd go there.

00:32:33.205 --> 00:32:34.260
JESSE MICHELS: Well
actually, yeah.

00:32:34.260 --> 00:32:35.030
I should go there.

00:32:35.030 --> 00:32:36.210
You kind of teed me off.

00:32:36.210 --> 00:32:38.846
Well, can you talk about those
trying times with Ariana?

00:32:38.846 --> 00:32:39.970
SCOOTER BRAUN: Look, it's--

00:32:39.970 --> 00:32:41.250
yeah.

00:32:41.250 --> 00:32:41.940
Glad you asked.

00:32:46.080 --> 00:32:47.160
I didn't see that coming.

00:32:50.080 --> 00:32:52.800
Look, Ariana-- very well
known-- had a terrorist attack

00:32:52.800 --> 00:32:56.070
at her show in Manchester.

00:32:56.070 --> 00:33:01.140
And over 20 people were killed,
including a 9-year-old girl

00:33:01.140 --> 00:33:02.760
and other kids.

00:33:02.760 --> 00:33:05.520
And she was there.

00:33:05.520 --> 00:33:08.070
And these people were
there to see her.

00:33:08.070 --> 00:33:12.294
And there's that guilt you
carry when that happens.

00:33:12.294 --> 00:33:12.960
And I was angry.

00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:15.168
Because of my grandparents
being Holocaust survivors,

00:33:15.168 --> 00:33:19.189
I always knew that kind of
evil existed in the world.

00:33:19.189 --> 00:33:21.480
And I'd kind of waited my
whole life for an opportunity

00:33:21.480 --> 00:33:22.810
to take it on.

00:33:22.810 --> 00:33:24.804
So I was, like,
rearing and ready to go

00:33:24.804 --> 00:33:25.720
and filled with anger.

00:33:25.720 --> 00:33:26.730
And I was like, we're
going to do a show.

00:33:26.730 --> 00:33:27.930
We're going to go back.

00:33:27.930 --> 00:33:32.340
And when I got to
her the next day,

00:33:32.340 --> 00:33:33.814
she, rightfully
so, was torn apart.

00:33:33.814 --> 00:33:35.730
And she was like, I don't
know if I could ever

00:33:35.730 --> 00:33:39.270
sing these songs again,
let alone go on stage.

00:33:39.270 --> 00:33:42.180
So I had to kind of pull
myself back and realize

00:33:42.180 --> 00:33:46.074
this wasn't a moment for me.

00:33:46.074 --> 00:33:47.490
And I worked on
canceling the tour

00:33:47.490 --> 00:33:48.948
and worked with
her insurance team.

00:33:48.948 --> 00:33:51.839
And the insurance
company was British,

00:33:51.839 --> 00:33:53.880
and they completely
understood and actually said,

00:33:53.880 --> 00:33:56.364
we're going to pay the
full fee for all her shows

00:33:56.364 --> 00:33:57.405
for the rest of the tour.

00:33:57.405 --> 00:34:00.060
We're going to fully
cover the insurance.

00:34:00.060 --> 00:34:01.104
And think about that.

00:34:01.104 --> 00:34:02.520
So now she's getting
her full fee,

00:34:02.520 --> 00:34:03.890
but she doesn't have
to pay for production.

00:34:03.890 --> 00:34:04.650
She doesn't have to
pay for the costumes.

00:34:04.650 --> 00:34:06.066
She doesn't have
to pay for staff.

00:34:06.066 --> 00:34:09.150
She's actually going to make
more money by not performing

00:34:09.150 --> 00:34:12.360
for the last two months than
she would on the entire tour,

00:34:12.360 --> 00:34:16.239
by just accepting the insurance.

00:34:16.239 --> 00:34:18.030
And by the time I flew
home two days later,

00:34:18.030 --> 00:34:20.111
I got home to 16 text
messages saying, call me.

00:34:20.111 --> 00:34:20.610
Call me.

00:34:20.610 --> 00:34:21.397
Call me.

00:34:21.397 --> 00:34:22.230
And I called her up.

00:34:22.230 --> 00:34:24.570
And she knew that
financial point.

00:34:24.570 --> 00:34:27.060
And she said, if I
don't do something,

00:34:27.060 --> 00:34:28.800
I'm not who I say I am.

00:34:28.800 --> 00:34:30.854
And all these kids
who come and see me

00:34:30.854 --> 00:34:33.300
and all the things I tell
them, they're not real.

00:34:33.300 --> 00:34:35.639
So what's the plan?

00:34:35.639 --> 00:34:37.839
And I said, look, I--

00:34:37.839 --> 00:34:39.630
she goes, I'm ready to
go on tour tomorrow.

00:34:39.630 --> 00:34:40.280
I want to go back.

00:34:40.280 --> 00:34:41.190
And I said, look,
I think you need

00:34:41.190 --> 00:34:43.773
to take some time to make sure
you're strong enough, because I

00:34:43.773 --> 00:34:45.360
think you're excited right now.

00:34:45.360 --> 00:34:48.639
But let's go back in two
weeks, because that's Paris.

00:34:48.639 --> 00:34:51.719
We'll cancel six shows
because you need time

00:34:51.719 --> 00:34:54.230
to heal and really take this in.

00:34:54.230 --> 00:34:56.882
And Paris is where the Eagles
of Death Metal happened,

00:34:56.882 --> 00:34:58.590
and I thought that
was a great statement.

00:34:58.590 --> 00:35:00.660
And I said, but I
have a crazier idea.

00:35:00.660 --> 00:35:05.730
Before Paris, instead of waiting
three, four months, a year,

00:35:05.730 --> 00:35:07.871
we should go back to
Manchester and perform.

00:35:07.871 --> 00:35:09.120
And she goes, do you think so?

00:35:09.120 --> 00:35:09.619
Why?

00:35:09.619 --> 00:35:11.672
And I said, because
the reason terrorists

00:35:11.672 --> 00:35:13.630
do this is they want to
change our way of life.

00:35:13.630 --> 00:35:15.940
They want to scare us.

00:35:15.940 --> 00:35:18.000
And the best way to stop
it from happening again

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:20.460
is answering right away
and answering in defiance

00:35:20.460 --> 00:35:22.085
and letting them know
they're not going

00:35:22.085 --> 00:35:23.340
to change our way of life.

00:35:23.340 --> 00:35:27.180
And she, without even
pausing, was like, I'm in.

00:35:27.180 --> 00:35:28.530
And we had two weeks.

00:35:28.530 --> 00:35:30.520
We put the show together.

00:35:30.520 --> 00:35:33.390
And I put a tremendous
amount of pressure

00:35:33.390 --> 00:35:35.970
on a small Italian
girl's shoulders.

00:35:35.970 --> 00:35:38.977
And she stepped up
and she handled it.

00:35:38.977 --> 00:35:40.560
And there were a lot
of amazing people

00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:41.768
who stepped up for that show.

00:35:41.768 --> 00:35:44.222
And that will always
go down in my mind

00:35:44.222 --> 00:35:45.930
as the most important
and most incredible

00:35:45.930 --> 00:35:47.370
show I've ever been a part of.

00:35:47.370 --> 00:35:50.910
To give you a little context,
we finally got back to the UK.

00:35:50.910 --> 00:35:52.410
We were rehearsing
the night before.

00:35:52.410 --> 00:35:55.920
Staying in Manchester, we
rehearsed at Wembley Arena

00:35:55.920 --> 00:35:57.540
the night before.

00:35:57.540 --> 00:36:01.379
And that night was the night
of the London Bridge attack.

00:36:01.379 --> 00:36:03.420
So the second terrorist
attack happened the night

00:36:03.420 --> 00:36:04.520
before our show.

00:36:04.520 --> 00:36:05.394
JESSE MICHELS: Wow.

00:36:05.394 --> 00:36:07.810
SCOOTER BRAUN: And that was
the first time I was thinking,

00:36:07.810 --> 00:36:12.229
is my excitement and arrogance
going to get people killed?

00:36:12.229 --> 00:36:14.520
And before I could even think
about canceling the show,

00:36:14.520 --> 00:36:16.950
Chris Martin from Coldplay--
he was in the show--

00:36:16.950 --> 00:36:17.730
sends me a text.

00:36:17.730 --> 00:36:19.230
Please don't cancel.

00:36:19.230 --> 00:36:21.150
And then Marcus
Mumford calls me,

00:36:21.150 --> 00:36:22.920
because I'd just seen
him at rehearsal.

00:36:22.920 --> 00:36:24.540
And says, do not cancel.

00:36:24.540 --> 00:36:26.940
It's more important than ever
that you guys do this show.

00:36:26.940 --> 00:36:28.945
Ariana, I never everyone
even talked to about,

00:36:28.945 --> 00:36:29.820
didn't even go there.

00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:32.190
She had already gone to sleep.

00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:34.710
And I spent the night,
talked to her mom.

00:36:34.710 --> 00:36:36.540
We decided to go
on with the show.

00:36:36.540 --> 00:36:38.310
And the Greater
Manchester Police

00:36:38.310 --> 00:36:41.700
wanted me to release a
statement on behalf of our team

00:36:41.700 --> 00:36:43.260
that the show was
going to go on.

00:36:43.260 --> 00:36:44.718
I spent the whole
night writing it.

00:36:44.718 --> 00:36:46.890
Woke up, put it out,
and I said that we

00:36:46.890 --> 00:36:49.260
have a greater responsibility
now more than ever

00:36:49.260 --> 00:36:51.990
to continue on this journey.

00:36:51.990 --> 00:36:54.000
Not only for the
victims of Manchester,

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:55.680
but the victims of
London, to honor them

00:36:55.680 --> 00:36:58.560
and be on that stage.

00:36:58.560 --> 00:37:01.230
And then the Manchester Police
put out a statement saying,

00:37:01.230 --> 00:37:02.710
the show will go on.

00:37:02.710 --> 00:37:06.210
However, please understand
that the alert is now

00:37:06.210 --> 00:37:08.500
at high, which means
there is, quote,

00:37:08.500 --> 00:37:11.350
"likely going to be an attack."

00:37:11.350 --> 00:37:14.050
And we were going
to be on YouTube--

00:37:14.050 --> 00:37:19.750
thanks-- Facebook, Twitter,
Capital Radio, BBC Radio,

00:37:19.750 --> 00:37:21.460
and the BBC.

00:37:21.460 --> 00:37:24.970
So you could watch our
entire show from your home.

00:37:24.970 --> 00:37:27.430
I was convinced no one
was going to show up.

00:37:27.430 --> 00:37:30.610
And when Marcus walked
out to open the show,

00:37:30.610 --> 00:37:32.794
the Mumford guys
weren't in town.

00:37:32.794 --> 00:37:34.960
It's the only time Marcus
Mumford has ever performed

00:37:34.960 --> 00:37:36.610
without Mumford and Sons.

00:37:36.610 --> 00:37:39.850
And he did "Timshel," and he
changed a couple of lyrics

00:37:39.850 --> 00:37:41.200
to honor the victims.

00:37:41.200 --> 00:37:42.616
And when he walked
out, there were

00:37:42.616 --> 00:37:44.290
60,000 people in the place.

00:37:44.290 --> 00:37:45.760
It was packed.

00:37:45.760 --> 00:37:48.550
And it was chills because it was
about to be a three, four hour

00:37:48.550 --> 00:37:49.420
show.

00:37:49.420 --> 00:37:52.570
And he and I talked beforehand
about how to start it.

00:37:52.570 --> 00:37:54.390
And we asked for a
moment of silence.

00:37:54.390 --> 00:37:57.010
And at the end, he said,
let's not be afraid.

00:37:57.010 --> 00:37:58.120
And the place roared.

00:37:58.120 --> 00:38:00.916
And it's something I'll never
forget for the rest of my life.

00:38:00.916 --> 00:38:02.290
JESSE MICHELS:
That's incredible.

00:38:02.290 --> 00:38:04.669
That's awesome that you guys
were able to stay the course

00:38:04.669 --> 00:38:05.460
and make it happen.

00:38:05.460 --> 00:38:06.667
Yeah, give it up.

00:38:06.667 --> 00:38:10.006
[APPLAUSE]

00:38:11.811 --> 00:38:12.310
OK.

00:38:12.310 --> 00:38:14.500
So I want to talk about Kanye.

00:38:17.020 --> 00:38:19.090
You've had a relationship
with Kanye for a while,

00:38:19.090 --> 00:38:22.330
but you signed him kind
of later in his career.

00:38:22.330 --> 00:38:26.800
Can you talk about what Kanye
means to you as a friend

00:38:26.800 --> 00:38:32.710
and as a colleague now and what
the future holds for Kanye?

00:38:32.710 --> 00:38:38.370
SCOOTER BRAUN: Look, he is
the most interesting person

00:38:38.370 --> 00:38:40.630
I've ever met in my life.

00:38:40.630 --> 00:38:42.180
He is a genius.

00:38:42.180 --> 00:38:43.600
And I've witnessed
and experienced

00:38:43.600 --> 00:38:45.930
that he truly is
a creative genius,

00:38:45.930 --> 00:38:48.570
because all my other
clients, a lot of it

00:38:48.570 --> 00:38:52.350
kind of comes on the
creativity, the ideas.

00:38:52.350 --> 00:38:54.920
A lot of it, myself
and team members,

00:38:54.920 --> 00:38:58.210
it's on us to kind of come up
with and then work with them.

00:38:58.210 --> 00:38:59.650
Kanye's always the person,
he's like, yeah I like that.

00:38:59.650 --> 00:39:00.240
But what about this?

00:39:00.240 --> 00:39:01.156
And you're like, damn.

00:39:01.156 --> 00:39:03.840
How did I not see that?

00:39:03.840 --> 00:39:06.600
But he's even made me
see colors differently.

00:39:06.600 --> 00:39:08.760
Like, we've spent
so much talking

00:39:08.760 --> 00:39:11.700
about colors and
palettes that I actually

00:39:11.700 --> 00:39:14.130
see colors and
aesthetic differently

00:39:14.130 --> 00:39:17.070
because of his education
of hours and hours

00:39:17.070 --> 00:39:18.377
and hours of conversation.

00:39:18.377 --> 00:39:20.460
JESSE MICHELS: Doesn't he
have synesthesia, like--

00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:20.930
SCOOTER BRAUN: Yeah, he does.

00:39:20.930 --> 00:39:22.454
JESSE MICHELS:
--sounds are color?

00:39:22.454 --> 00:39:24.620
SCOOTER BRAUN: When he hears
sounds, he sees colors.

00:39:24.620 --> 00:39:26.200
JESSE MICHELS: Crazy.

00:39:26.200 --> 00:39:29.530
SCOOTER BRAUN: And we were
friends for a long time.

00:39:29.530 --> 00:39:32.160
If you look up the
Ludacris "Stand Up" video,

00:39:32.160 --> 00:39:37.650
I am the promoter, club owner
jumping around dancing in it.

00:39:37.650 --> 00:39:40.320
And Kanye produced that song,
and he makes a cameo in it.

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:43.290
And we actually met then before
he had just signed to the Roc,

00:39:43.290 --> 00:39:45.180
and he was a
producer, and no one

00:39:45.180 --> 00:39:47.100
knew who Kanye West
was other than if you'd

00:39:47.100 --> 00:39:47.930
worked with him as producer.

00:39:47.930 --> 00:39:49.770
And we met on that
set and were friendly.

00:39:49.770 --> 00:39:51.750
And kind of over the years,
always knew each other.

00:39:51.750 --> 00:39:54.166
His original manager, John
Monopoly, was always good to me

00:39:54.166 --> 00:39:57.210
when I was a younger guy.

00:39:57.210 --> 00:40:00.330
And then when he put up a
tweet saying he was $52 million

00:40:00.330 --> 00:40:02.040
in debt, he's my friend.

00:40:02.040 --> 00:40:05.370
So I texted him, are you OK?

00:40:05.370 --> 00:40:09.180
And I guess a lot of people
didn't ask him if he was OK.

00:40:09.180 --> 00:40:11.760
So he called me
back just to talk.

00:40:11.760 --> 00:40:13.470
And after talking
for about an hour,

00:40:13.470 --> 00:40:15.690
he said, you know, you
need to come work with me.

00:40:15.690 --> 00:40:18.750
And I said, Kanye, we've
talked about this before.

00:40:18.750 --> 00:40:19.810
I don't want to do that.

00:40:19.810 --> 00:40:22.017
Like, I'm afraid
of working with you

00:40:22.017 --> 00:40:23.850
because I don't want
to lose the friendship.

00:40:23.850 --> 00:40:24.787
I love you, dude.

00:40:24.787 --> 00:40:26.370
No, no, you need to
come work with me.

00:40:26.370 --> 00:40:27.682
You need to manage me.

00:40:27.682 --> 00:40:28.640
I'm going to call Izzy.

00:40:28.640 --> 00:40:29.556
You need to manage me.

00:40:29.556 --> 00:40:31.625
And I said, no,
no, no, we're good.

00:40:31.625 --> 00:40:33.000
Why don't we--
when are you back?

00:40:33.000 --> 00:40:33.916
You're back in a week?

00:40:33.916 --> 00:40:35.310
OK, you're back in a week.

00:40:35.310 --> 00:40:36.367
We'll talk about it then.

00:40:36.367 --> 00:40:38.700
And I thought this is like
the eighth time he and I have

00:40:38.700 --> 00:40:39.908
had a conversation like that.

00:40:39.908 --> 00:40:41.070
We're going to get it.

00:40:41.070 --> 00:40:42.469
We'll stay friends.

00:40:42.469 --> 00:40:44.760
The next morning, I get a
call from Adidas and Def Jam.

00:40:44.760 --> 00:40:47.160
So we're told you're the
manager and to deal with you.

00:40:47.160 --> 00:40:49.076
And that is how I became
Kanye West's manager.

00:40:51.900 --> 00:40:53.370
But he's become like a brother.

00:40:53.370 --> 00:40:56.130
And I joke around that it's
been 2 and 1/2 years now

00:40:56.130 --> 00:40:58.890
and I think we'll
always be friends

00:40:58.890 --> 00:41:00.810
and we'll always find
ways to work together,

00:41:00.810 --> 00:41:03.600
because we both have
this feeling of,

00:41:03.600 --> 00:41:04.920
art can change the world.

00:41:07.570 --> 00:41:10.074
And I joke around all the time
that I'm his manager today,

00:41:10.074 --> 00:41:11.240
but I might not be tomorrow.

00:41:11.240 --> 00:41:15.820
Like, I've lasted
longer than most.

00:41:15.820 --> 00:41:18.660
But I'm going to be
with him next week

00:41:18.660 --> 00:41:20.100
and I saw him last week.

00:41:20.100 --> 00:41:23.200
And he knows it.

00:41:23.200 --> 00:41:24.970
He's like, someday
when you're older,

00:41:24.970 --> 00:41:27.428
you're going to say you managed
Kanye West and that's cool.

00:41:27.428 --> 00:41:29.470
And I'm like, it's
cool right now, bro.

00:41:29.470 --> 00:41:31.470
I mean, we walked in, you
were like nice Yeezys.

00:41:31.470 --> 00:41:33.820
I was like, you're
goddamn right.

00:41:33.820 --> 00:41:36.230
JESSE MICHELS: He's
like, I got a hook up.

00:41:36.230 --> 00:41:38.664
SCOOTER BRAUN: But he
really is a genius.

00:41:38.664 --> 00:41:40.830
And here's a thing I like
to say about him publicly,

00:41:40.830 --> 00:41:41.700
because I don't like
to talk about it

00:41:41.700 --> 00:41:43.950
too much publicly out of
respect for that's not really

00:41:43.950 --> 00:41:45.280
